Trade/Device Name(s): ImmunoCAP Allergen i3, Common wasp venom (Yellow jacket)
ImmunoCAP Allergen i4, Paper wasp venom
Analyte(s): Specific IgE to Common wasp venom (Yellow jacket)
Specific IgE to Paper wasp venom
Document Summary: FDA 510(k) summary for ImmunoCAP Allergen i3 (Common wasp venom) and i4 (Paper wasp venom) reagents for measurement of specific IgE using Phadia instruments.
Indications for Use Summary: Quantitative in vitro assay to measure allergen specific IgE in human serum or plasma (EDTA or Na-Heparin) as an aid in clinical diagnosis of IgE mediated allergic disorders, to be used with Phadia 100, 250, 1000, 2500, and 5000 instruments in clinical laboratories.
